## Parallel platform development

<!-- PROJECT: Only relevant if your project ships on multiple
platforms (web + desktop, library + CLI + service, server + mobile,
etc.).  If single-platform, delete this section and the next.  The
Netcanon source uses this section to enforce that web and desktop
shells stay at feature parity. -->

`<PROJECT_NAME>` ships on `<N>` platforms.  All must be kept at feature
parity.

| Platform | Package | Entry point |
|---|---|---|
| `<PLATFORM_A>` | `<package_name>` | `<entry command>` |
| `<PLATFORM_B>` | `<package_name>` | `<entry command>` |

**Rule:** whenever a functional feature is added or changed on one
platform, the equivalent must be implemented on the other platform in
the same commit (or the same branch, if it spans multiple commits).
Never leave one platform behind.

This applies to:
- New API endpoints / public functions
- New UI surfaces
- New schema fields persisted to disk
- New external integrations
- New application settings that affect behaviour

